         <div xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve" type="translation">
            <p>
               <milestone n="1" unit="line"/> Year three of Imperator Caesar <milestone n="2" unit="line"/> Traianus Hadrianus Augustus. Work
                      done <milestone n="3" unit="line"/> for five days on the dyke works <milestone n="4" unit="line"/> for the same 3rd year, Mesore 4-8, <milestone n="5" unit="line"/> at
                      the canal of Pholemis, on behalf of Theadelphia, <milestone n="6" unit="line"/> by Demas, son of Heras
                      and Tausiris, grandson of Petesuchos. <milestone n="7" unit="line"/> Signed by me, N. N.
                      <note>Translation: P.J. Sijpesteijn – K.A. Worp, BASP 16 (1979) 132 Nr. 1</note>
            </p>
